text: The 2009 Philippine region typhoon season was the period that tropical cyclones formed in the Western Pacific Ocean. The season ran throughout the year during 2009, with most tropical cyclones forming between May and November.The Philippine Atmospheric, Geophysical and Astronomical Services Administration (PAGASA) assigns names to tropical cyclones (including tropical depressions) that enter or form in the Philippine area of responsibility. These names, however, are not in common use outside of the Philippines. During the season, 39 tropical depressions developed within the Western Pacific, whilst 2 formed outside the region before moving into the Western Pacific. == Storms == === Philippines === *Tropical Depression Auring *Tropical Depression Bising *Typhoon Crising *Typhoon Dante *Typhoon Emong *Tropical Storm Feria *Tropical Depression Gorio *Tropical Depression Huaning *Typhoon Isang *Tropical Depression Jolina *Tropical Storm Kiko *Tropical Storm Labuyo *Tropical Depression Maring *Typhoon Nando *Typhoon Ondoy *Typhoon Pepemg *Typhoon Quedan *Typhoon Ramil *Tropical Storm Santi *Tropical Depression Tino *Tropical Depression Urduja *Tropical Depression Vinta Category:2009 in weather Category:Pacific typhoon seasons
